article.headline: Jacksonville 64, Savannah St. 54
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Glenn Powell had 16 points and 10 rebounds and Jacksonville never trailed in defeating Savannah State 64-54 on Tuesday night. The Dolphins (1-1) bounced back after a sluggish second half Friday night that cost them a potential upset win over Miami. Powell was 6 of 8 from the field and hit 4 of 6 free throws. Ayron Hardy added 14 points and seven assists for Jacksonville. The Dolphins jumped out to an 8-0 lead and led 29-12 with 6:19 to go. The Tigers (1-2) closed out the half on a 14-5 run -- including two 3-pointers from Keierre Richards and one from Jovonni Shuler -- to trail 34-26 at halftime. Jacksonville led by as many as 18 with 15:29 to go, but Savannah State pulled within eight points at 61-53 with 1:17 left. The Dolphins then hit 3 of 4 free throws to seal the win. Richards led Savannah State with 17 points and Shuler had 13.
